rich_message.text: I think I’ll never use the ENB elevators again
‼️ posting this for awareness and TO ask for help ‼️
I want to get this off my chest kasi until now, traumatized pa rin ako sa ginawa sakin ng isang student, kung sino ka man.

Around 10:56 AM yesterday, kaka-dismiss lang namin and nasa 7th floor pa kami ng engineering building. Our next class was at 11:00 AM sa 6th floor ng Tech. Siyempre, nagmamadali kami kasi kailangan pa mag-prepare at lilipat ng building. Alam namin kung gaano katagal pumila sa elevators kasi yung iba sira pa. Luckily, may elevator na nagbukas. We thought kasya kami so sumakay kami. May ilang humabol din na students, and since may space pa, sumakay sila.

Pero pagka-close ng door, out of nowhere, bigla akong tinulak. Not just lightly eh, yung tulak na padabog, agresibo, na para bang wala kang respeto. I froze for a second kasi nagulat ako sa ganung behavior. I tried to move a little kasi baka sobrang nasisikipan na siya. Hindi naman kami naglalaro or naghaharutan ng friends ko. Ni hindi nga ako nakikipag-usap habang nasa loob. Alam ko yung proper behavior sa elevator. The thing is, nasa likod yung bag ko, and baka nasiksik siya because of that. And yes, kasalanan ko rin for not immediately putting it in front, but what made my blood boil was how she handled it. She didn’t say a single word. She pushed me hard. Multiple times. As if she was entitled to that space more than anyone else.

Habang bumababa yung elevator, she kept pushing me in a padabog way. That’s when I turned and looked at her, and she finally opened her mouth, saying nasisikipan daw siya and that I should put my bag in front. I had already tried to distance myself nung una pa lang niya akong tinulak. I even said sorry calmly kahit siya na yung rude sa simula pa lang.

Wala akong intention na maniknik ng tao, I wasn’t moving around pls lang. I was also struggling to move my bag sa harap kasi nga masikip na. And just when I was about to remove my bag to give her peace, she crossed the line. Without hesitation, hinila niya yung strap ng bag ko off my shoulder like she had full authority over my own body and belongings. That wasn’t just rude eh. That was violating. I can still remember you saying "kuya, yung bag dapat nilalagay sa harap hindi sa likod.." nung bigla mong ginrab  yung strap ng bag ko.

I was triggered. Hindi ko alam kung nanghahamon siya ng away, but I chose to remain calm. Still, I felt helpless eh na parang wala akong choice and she acted like may full authority siya na basta-basta hubarin yung bag ko from my body. Do you even realize how demeaning that felt? I was left standing there na mukhang helpless at para bang wala akong magawa but to let her do whatever she wanted.

I decided not to escalate things further. Wala na rin akong energy makipag-away. I’ve started feeling sick lately, and my body’s been tired kasi I also teach students every Sunday. That’s why I just endured it quietly, but deep inside, gusto ko na siyang awayin sa ganung asal niya at that moment.

Paglabas namin, I looked at her face. Naka-grey hoodie, may hikaw, medyo kulot, pero di ko nakita yung ID kung taga-Main or Tech siya para ma identify and meport sa Discipline Unit. Alam kong nakikita niya kami while walking, pero she didn’t even care to look at me na para bang unbothered and even proud pa sa ginawa niya.

Hanggang sa discussion ng next subject, di ako makafocus kasi naiisip ko pa rin yung pagtulak niya at yung biglang paghila ng bag ko. The way she acted na feeling entitled and arrogant? Sobrang nakakabastos at nakakatrigger.

Ate, you could’ve behaved better if you had even just a little human decency. I never intended na masikipan ka, and sorry kung di ko nailagay agad yung bag ko sa harap. You could’ve simply said “Excuse me, nasisikipan ako.” But no, you chose aggression sa una pa lang.

I even talked about this with my friends, and they noticed na yung kasama mo, inirapan pa yung isa kong kaibigan nung nakasakay kami. We don’t know if you guys were having a bad day, pero monday na monday and umagang-umaga pa lang, may ganung behavior na. Mahirap intindihin yung ganung ugali niyo, to be honest.

For my fellow students reading this, I’m posting this for awareness and to ask for help: possible po ba na ma-request yung CCTV footage from that elevator so I can have evidence and formally report this to the Discipline Department? I don’t want this to happen again to other students who might ride the elevator with them, especially her.
No one deserves to be pushed around and treated like someone owns the place!
